post_text: Congratulations to Mobile County principal Michelle Dubose Adams for being named one of the top 10 principals in the United States. The U.S. Department of Education just announced that Adams, as principal of Eichold-Mertz School of Math and Science, has received the Terrell H. Bell Award for Outstanding School Leadership. She will receive the award in Washington, D.C., next month as Eichold-Mertz will be recognized as a National Blue Ribbon School
shared_text:
Mobile County Public Schools
October 23, 2019 at 5:00 PM ·

BREAKING NEWS. Our very own Michelle Dubose Adams has been named one of the top 10 principals in the United States. The U.S. Department of Education just announced that Adams, as principal of Eichold-Mertz School of Math and Science, has received the Terrell H. Bell Award for Outstanding School Leadership. She will receive the award in Washington, D.C., next month as Eichold-Mertz will be recognized as a National Blue Ribbon School
